y to Allah, I seek your forgiveness","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 10, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said these words often before he passed away, \u201cGlory be to Allah and with His praise. I seek Your forgiveness and I repent to You.\u201d I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, I see you have said these words\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34698,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/12\/19\/ibn-masud-ayat-istighfar\/","url_meta":{"origin":11238,"position":1},"title":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud on Tawbah: Two verses to seek forgiveness from Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 19, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Alqamah reported: Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cVerily, there are two verses in the Book of Allah, never does a servant commit a sin, recite them both, and seek forgiveness from Allah but that Allah will forgive him. His saying: Those who, if they behave\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":406,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/01\/23\/prophet-teaches-abu-bakr-istighfar\/","url_meta":{"origin":11238,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Istighfar: The Prophet teaches Abu Bakr to seek forgiveness","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 23, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Bakr\u00a0reported: He\u00a0said to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, \"O Messenger of Allah, teach me a supplication to say in my prayers.\" The Prophet said, \"Say: O Allah, I have wronged myself with great injustices and none forgives sin but You, so forgive me and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15909,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/09\/04\/seek-forgiveness-believers\/","url_meta":{"origin":11238,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Istighfar: Seek forgiveness for yourself and believers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 4, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Sarjis reported: I met\u00a0the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and I ate a meal of stew\u00a0with him. I said, \u201cI ask Allah to forgive you, O Prophet.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cYes, and for you as well.\u201d Then the Prophet\u00a0recited the verse, \u201cSeek forgiveness for your sins\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2780,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/05\/janazah-prophet-najashi-negus\/","url_meta":{"origin":11238,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Najashi: The Prophet prays funeral prayer for King of Abyssinia","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 5, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, told us about the Negus, the ruler of Abyssinia, on the day he died. The Prophet said to us, \u201cSeek forgiveness for your brother.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1263, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 951 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25554,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/06\/dua-qiyam-al-layl-takbir\/","url_meta":{"origin":11238,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Dua: The Prophet&#8217;s night prayer routine","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 6, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Shariq al-Hawzani reported: I entered the home of Aisha, may Allah be pleased with her, and I asked her, \u201cHow did the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, begin his prayer when he awakened at night?\u201d Aisha said, \u201cWhen the Prophet awakened at night, he would exalt\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/11238","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\